OL,3,CLack of support leaves mother, 78,
OL,4,Ccaring for bedbound son
OL,6,FIn response, a spokesperson from
OL,7,FHealth and Care Jersey says: "We are
OL,8,Funable to comment on individual cases.
OL,9,FIf an islander requires social care,
OL,10,Fthe primary route is funding through
OL,11,Fthe Long Term Care scheme.
OL,13,F"Where the need for support cannot be
OL,14,Ffully met within Long Term Care
OL,15,Fprovision, Health and Care Jersey will
OL,16,Fconsider additional provision based on
OL,17,Findividual circumstance and need.
